h3. Issue Summary
There are a few conditions that can lead to this problem:
- Copying a page with body causes the image not be shown on the page.
- Adding an attachment after the page has been created without the image.

h3. Steps to Reproduce

h3. Steps to Reproduce: Case #1 - Page Copy
 # create a parent page: <site>/<space>/pages/402325512/DEVHELP-7212+-+parent+page
 # create a source page: <site>/<space>/pages/402161672/DEVHELP-7212+\-\+copy+page+\-+broken+attachments+\-+source+page. Notice that the attachment here is called background.png
 # copy the page but provide a body with an attachment called image.png
{code}
curl --request POST \
  --url '<site>/wiki/rest/api/content/402161672/copy' \
  --header 'Accept: application/json;charset=UTF-8' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --data '{
   "copyAttachments": true,
   "copyPermissions": false,
   "copyProperties": false,
   "copyLabels": true,
   "copyCustomContents": false,
   "destination": {
     "type": "parent_page",
     "value": "402325512"
   },
   "pageTitle": "DEVHELP-7212 - Target Page 1",
   "body": {
      "storage": {
       "representation": "storage",
       "value": "<ac:image><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image>"
     }
   }
}' \
--basic --user '<userEmail>:<token>'
{code}
# create another page which is going to be the source for the image: <site>/<space>/pages/402489345/DEVHELP-7212+\-+source+page+image+only. The attachment here is called image.png
# copy the new page (the one with the source image) with the existing_page with id 402456577 as the target page
{code}
curl --request POST \
  --url '<site>/wiki/rest/api/content/402489345/copy' \
  --header 'Accept: application/json;charset=UTF-8' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --data '{
   "copyAttachments": true,
   "copyPermissions": false,
   "copyProperties": false,
   "copyLabels": true,
   "copyCustomContents": false,
   "destination": {
     "type": "existing_page",
     "value": "402456577"
   },
   "pageTitle": "DEVHELP-7212 - Target Page 1",
   "body": {
      "storage": {
       "representation": "storage",
       "value": "<ac:image><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image>"
     }
   }
}' \
--basic --user '<userEmail>:<token>'
{code}

h3. Steps to Reproduce: Case #2 - Adding an attachment at a later stage
# Create a page with a {{image.png}} in the body
{noformat}
curl --request POST \
  --url '<site>/wiki/rest/api/content' \
  --header 'Accept: application/json;charset=UTF-8' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --data '{
  "type": "page",
  "title": "DEVHELP-7234-1",
  "space": { "key": "FIRSTSPACE" },
  "ancestors": [{ "type": "page", "id": "98306" }],
  "body": {
    "storage": {
      "value": "<ac:image ac:align=\"center\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image.png\" /></ac:image>",
      "representation": "storage"
    }
  }
}' \
--basic --user '<userEmail>:<token>'
{noformat}
# Upload the attachment called {{image.png}}
{noformat}
curl -D- \
  --url <site>/wiki/rest/api/content/405635073/child/attachment \
  -X POST \
  -H 'X-Atlassian-Token: nocheck' \
  -F 'file=@"image.png"' \
  -F 'minorEdit="true"' \
  -F 'comment="Example attachment comment"; type=image/png' \
  --basic --user '<userEmail>:<token>'
{noformat}

h3. Expected Results
The image on the target page is correctly shown.

h3. Actual Results
The result will be the following on the target page <site>/<space>/pages/402456577/DEVHELP-7212+\-+Target+Page+1:
- the image doesn’t show on the page
- the attachments are on the page. Both of them are correct and can be loaded from the Attachments page.

h3. Workaround
If a site is affected, the problem can be addressed by changing a feature flag setting.

Please raise a ticket with the Atlassian customer support team at https://support.atlassian.com/contact/ and mention this ticket so that a support representative can update the relevant feature flag on the site.

h3. Issue Summary

When navigating through Confluence pages that have [Jira issues|https://support.atlassian.com/confluence-cloud/docs/insert-the-jira-issues-macro/] or [Jira charts|https://support.atlassian.com/confluence-cloud/docs/insert-the-jira-chart-macro/], instead of having the content for these macros rendering, the following errors will be displayed intermittently:

{code}
com.atlassian.sal.api.net.ResponseException: java.net.SocketTimeoutException: Read timed out 
{code}

{code}
Unable to render JIRA issues macro. Connection to JIRA has timed out.
{code}

h3. Steps to Reproduce

# Add different Jira charts or macros to pages.
# View these pages from time to time.

h3. Expected Results

The macros will always have their content rendered.

h3. Actual Results

The following error messages are displayed instead of the macros. Note that the issue itself gets "fixed" from time to time.

{code}
com.atlassian.sal.api.net.ResponseException: java.net.SocketTimeoutException: Read timed out 
{code}

{code}
Unable to render JIRA issues macro. Connection to JIRA has timed out.
{code}

h3. Workaround

Manually edit the page and the macros to re-insert the same content.

h3. Issue Summary
When searching content within the searching macros from MS Teams, we are not able to retrieve any result.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a page on Confluence;
# Insert either the [Livesearch|https://support.atlassian.com/confluence-cloud/docs/insert-the-livesearch-macro/] or the [Page Tree Search|https://support.atlassian.com/confluence-cloud/docs/insert-the-page-tree-search-macro/] macro in the page;
# Publish it;
# On MS Teams, connect to this page you just created;
# Within MS Teams, access the page you connected and try to perform any search in the macros. 

h3. Expected Results
The search works as expected.

h3. Actual Results
You get an error that either result in:
{code}{}{code}
Or
{code}"error": "An unhandled error occurred. We are working on it!{code}

*Note*
* This is an issue that is happening on the latest version of the Confluence Cloud app for MS Teams (version 1.1.1).

h3. Workaround
Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-12638].
  {panel}

This request has come from a customer's post on the Atlassian Confluence Forum:
{noformat}
in our confluence installation we have several spaces with restricted access.
So when users with restricted access search, he will get also a list of labels from other spaces where he has no access.
This is very irritating. Since we like to seach with related labels, but we can't use this because we see labels from spaces where we don't have acces.
{noformat}

h3. Issue Summary
The Children Display macro links are set as header 6, so as they are not properly said headers in the page, the ToC macro will get lost and won't behave well when exporting the page to PDF.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a page named _Parent_;
# Add a *Table of Contents* macro - set it to show the section number;
# Add a *Children Display* macro;
# Insert a few headers in the page, so it gets populated in the ToC macro;
# Publish it;
# Create a child page under _Parent_, named _Child_;
# Publish it;
# Go back to the _Parent_ page;
# Export it to PDF and open the file.

h3. Expected Results
Everything is shown as expected.

h3. Actual Results
The ToC macro shows an error: {{Error rendering macro 'toc' : null}}

*Notes*
* If you do not uncheck the section number option for the ToC macro, it will display the child page as the first header in the macro;
* In the page's HTML code, the link to the child page (from the Children Display macro) is set as {{h6}}, that's why it gets broken.

h3. Workaround
Under the Table of Contents macro, set the field _Maximum Heading Level_ to 5, so it won't consider the links from the Children Display macro.
